<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Design logo with photoshop and import it to game]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=11662&amp;p=134313#p134313"><![CDATA[
I don't know how to do it in Adobe® Photoshop® software, but in GNU Image Manipulation Program (GIMP), you can try this:<br /><ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>Create a new image the same size as the image you want to convert. </li><li>Fill the image with one of the four colors in the desired pattern. </li><li>Using the pencil tool, draw at least one pixel of each of the three other colors. </li><li>Image &gt; Mode &gt; Indexed. </li><li>Colors &gt; Map &gt; Rearrange Colormap and drag the colors into the same order that they appear in the emulator's palette viewer. </li><li>Copy the image you want to convert and paste it into the new image's window. </li></ol><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Fri Sep 26, 2014 4:02 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
