I am translating Captain Tsubasa Vol. II - Super Striker (J) [!].nes to Persian<br />I want to make a logo for its title screen<br /><br />This is the original title screen :<br /><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/gtmujv0v3kppwu0jyxs6.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I design the logo with photoshop :<br /><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/ws4wsu4r7z10c97toc0t.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />As you can see I used only 4 colors to design it :<br /><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/8bpxuaw6zran7anuiv8b.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I change it to Indexed Color :<br /><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/v99ap85v307xusb52vfe.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I save it as BMP 8bit :<br /><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/ken0huxkb25rdvhr3gtj.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I open the logo with paint (on windows xp) and copy it :<br /><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/q6u6riw3n8s5hcoyfwea.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I open the game with YY-CHR.NET and past the logo in it :<br /><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/z8hz8f5hxke58ddbyhh2.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />But the problem is that the colors of the logo aren't in their place<br />For example the color inside of A must be 17 (orange)  and the background must be 0C (Blue) <br />So that the logo appears with the correct colors inside of the game <br />How can I import the logo into the game in a way that the colors match the colors of the original logo of the game?<br /><img src="http://8pic.ir/images/s1s2f13fyspjk38lc8jn.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />Thanks in advance<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=4330">FARID</a> — Fri Sep 26, 2014 3:08 pm</p><hr />
